title: Button/ValidValues/SetTitleValidState
description: Button validValues with setTitle — valid state highlights correct button
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki-multiple
tags: [[$:/tags/wiki-test-spec]]

title: Narrative

This test verifies that `validValues` does not interfere with normal operation when using `setTitle`. The state tiddler text is `OptionB`, which is in `validValues`, so button ''B'' should be highlighted with a red background.
+
title: $:/state/test-btn
text: OptionB
+
title: Output

\whitespace trim

<style>
.selected { background-color: red; color: white; }
</style>

<$button setTitle="$:/state/test-btn"
	setTo="OptionA"
	default="OptionA"
	validValues="OptionA OptionB"
	selectedClass="selected"
>
	A
</$button>
<$button setTitle="$:/state/test-btn"
	setTo="OptionB"
	default="OptionA"
	validValues="OptionA OptionB"
	selectedClass="selected"
>
	B
</$button>
+
title: ExpectedResult

<p><style>.selected { background-color: red; color: white; }</style></p><p><button aria-checked="false" class="">A</button><button aria-checked="true" class=" selected">B</button></p>